    "name": "Cautious Clay",
    "profile": "Josh Karpeh was born on January 30, 1993 in Cleveland, Ohio. He began playing flute at seven and picked up saxophone to join his high school jazz band. Karpeh attended college at George Washington University where he minored in Jazz. After graduating from George Washington, he moved to Brooklyn, New York, where he currently resides.\r\n\r\nDuring his time at George Washington University, Karpeh first began to learn music production by making beats for friends and doing remixes. His production style was largely influenced by SoundCloud. On December 14, 2015, he released a remix for Billie Eilish’s song \"Ocean Eyes\" on SoundCloud and, on November 18, 2016, the remix was included as one of four other official remixes on the Ocean Eyes (The Remixes) EP. On September 22, 2017, he released \"Cold War\", the first single from his debut EP, Blood Type, which was first released on February 21, 2018, and then re-released on April 13, 2018 with the additional single \"Stolen Moments\". Cautious Clay's de",
